• Team building events with: IEEE Alexandria, PVH Cairo, and Unilever Egypt.

The Middle East Council for Small Business & Entrepreneurship (MCSBE) supports entrepreneurs and small businesses by offering training programs, business competitions, seed funding and community building services to businesses from all over Egypt. Responsible for: 
• Co-designing and overseeing execution of all programs and projects for small businesses and entrepreneurs in Egypt, including business development and team management; 
• Budget allocation and financial overview;
• Partnership outreach and strategy development.

MCSBE is the regional affiliate of the International Council for Small Business (ICSB).

IMI's work focussed on inclusive policy making and connecting societal movements to the right policy makers. Some of the larger projects I was involved with: 
• International research on open government and transparency mechanisms for the ministry of Internal Affairs;
• Monitoring and evaluating the National Innovation conference for the ministry of Infrastructure & Environment;
• Process design and future exploration for the Dutch National Delta Programme for the Department of Waterways and Public Works;
• Co-creating parliamentary sessions on a more transparent Freedom of Information Act (Wob) for GroenLinks;
• Project assistant ‘Information & Politics’ on the information position of Parliament, interviewing MPs, translating texts and organising events on parliamentary self-reflection through “het presidium”.
